ZH: 这个工厂雇佣了很多苦力来做体力活。
EN: This factory hires many coolies to do laborious work.

ZH: 在历史上，苦力被用来进行建筑和铁路建设。
EN: In the past, coolies were used for building construction and railroad development.

ZH: 城市工地上常见苦力在搬运重物。
EN: Coolies are often seen carrying heavy loads on urban construction sites.

ZH: 这位苦力是农村里的农民转行来城市打工的。
EN: This coolie is a farmer from the countryside who came to the city to work.

ZH: 他们用鼓励的话语激励苦力努力工作。
EN: They motivate coolies to work hard with encouraging words.

ZH: 苦力们每天都在承受很大的体力劳动。
EN: Coolies endure strenuous physical labor every day.

ZH: 这里的苦力都是来自不同地区的。
EN: The coolies here come from different regions.

ZH: 许多苦力在贫困地区找不到其他的工作。
EN: Many coolies cannot find other jobs in impoverished areas.

ZH: 这座矿山雇佣了大量的苦力来开采资源。
EN: This mine employs a large number of coolies to extract resources.

ZH: 在这个工厂里，苦力们被要求每天工作十小时以上。
EN: In this factory, coolies are required to work more than ten hours a day.

ZH: 这些苦力需要学习新的技能以适应市场需求。
EN: These coolies need to learn new skills to meet market demands.

ZH: 城市里有很多苦力在建筑工地上工作。
EN: There are many coolies working on construction sites in the city.

ZH: 小贩市场上的苦力们来自贫困地区。
EN: The coolies in the street markets come from impoverished areas.

ZH: 雨后，苦力们需要清理泥泞的工地。
EN: After the rain, coolies need to clean up the muddy construction site.

ZH: 学徒苦力需要跟随师傅学习技术。
EN: Apprentice coolies need to learn skills from their master.

ZH: 贵公司是否会雇佣外来的苦力来完成项目？
EN: Will your company employ migrant coolies to complete the project?

ZH: 这个国家的政府正在采取措施保护苦力的权益。
EN: The government of this country is taking measures to protect the rights of coolies.

ZH: 大多数苦力都来自农村家庭。
EN: Most coolies come from rural families.

ZH: 身体力行是苦力们的特点之一。
EN: Physical labor is one of the characteristics of coolies.

ZH: 这座工厂里的苦力们有限的工资待遇引发了争议。
EN: The limited salary treatment of coolies in this factory has caused controversy.
